    "31 Von Foerster emphasizes the difference between recognition/recall (a fundamentally computational, dynamic, inference process) and mere storage/retrieval [71,100].",
    "32 In this scheme, we can think of the Left and Right sides of the bowtie architecture (Figure 2B) as two agents, having to communicate via a narrow interface in-between, like language that helps complex beings cooperate through a low-bandwidth interface.Being agential/intelligent means, you do not track microstates -the communication channel doesn't preserve the lowest level -bits -it preserves meaning or saliency.",
    "In biology, this is essential because the parts are never guaranteed to preserve low-level details; engineers make cables where the slightest change of pinout can destroy the functionality; biology assumes there will be \"pins\" missing, reversed, hacked, etc.",
    "and that it will have to spend effort to decode and extract meaning not dependent on the microstates of the message.",
    "This is why one can inject brain homogenate blindly into a recipient in a memory transfer experiment, and perhaps why you can randomize the pixel elements of a photo of a dog and the ANN still recognizes the dog-ness of it."
